    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Generally applied to a variety of tables used for dressing and conducting one's toilet; they may be fitted with a mirror and drawers to hold toilet articles such as brushes and combs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000002851/Aronson, Encyclopedia of Furniture (1965)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Generalmente aplicado a una variedad de mesas empleadas para tocado, normalmente acondicionadas con un espejo y que tienen cajones para guardar artículos de tocador tales como cepillos y peinetas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Benaming die van toepassing is op verschillende tafels waaraan toilet kan worden gemaakt, meestal met een spiegel en laden waarin toiletartikelen liggen zoals borstels en kammen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
